The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Smooth run for Ruia twins
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Smooth run for Ruia twins
                            
	Calcutta, Jan. 29 (PTI): City-based Dunlop India Ltd today reported a net profit of Rs 63 lakh for the third quarter ended December 2009.        
	The company had suffered a net loss of Rs 6.90 crore in the corresponding period last year.         
	Net sales rose 10 per cent to Rs 40.73 crore over the corresponding period a year ago.        
	On the results, Ruia Group chairman Pawan K. Ruia said, With both the plants at Sahaganj and Ambattur operational, the future for Dunlop looks bright.        
	Dunlop has resumed trading on the bourses after a gap of almost eight years. Out of 7,19,82,875 issued, subscribed and fully paid equity shares, 4,49,89,297 are permitted to be traded on the Bombay Stock Exchange since January 12.        
	The matter for listing of balance shares is pending before Delhi High Court, Ruia said.         
	Falcon net        
	Bangalore-based Falcon Tyres Ltd  a Ruia Group firm  has reported a sharp jump in net profit at Rs 11.65 crore for the third quarter ended December 31 against Rs 61 lakh in the year-ago period.        
	Falcon has started reaping the benefits of continuous expansion of its capacity. Since signing a technical aid agreement with Sumitomo Rubber Industries of Japan in 2007, the company has increased its capacity to 900,000 tyres per month and commissioned a 6mw co-generation plant at Mysore, Ruia said.        
	Net sales stood at Rs 166.66 crore, up from Rs 119.15 crore a year ago.                                                                                                                                       
